WEBVTT

00:00:02.906 --> 00:00:05.046
(Episode 25)

00:00:18.626 --> 00:00:19.786
You knew, didn't you?

00:00:22.956 --> 00:00:24.326
You knew how I felt.

00:00:31.066 --> 00:00:32.266
I knew.

00:00:40.506 --> 00:00:41.816
And I knew, too.

00:00:43.676 --> 00:00:46.246
I knew what your answer would be. But still...

00:00:48.016 --> 00:00:49.416
Even though I knew you'd reject me,

00:00:51.656 --> 00:00:53.356
I just had to tell you.

00:00:55.696 --> 00:00:56.856
Figures.

00:00:59.366 --> 00:01:00.866
You never say what you should at the right time,

00:01:02.396 --> 00:01:04.906
but you have no problem saying what you shouldn't.

00:01:09.436 --> 00:01:10.736
We're not...

00:01:11.446 --> 00:01:13.276
a good match.

00:01:14.376 --> 00:01:15.616
You...

00:01:17.046 --> 00:01:18.116
don't suit me.

00:01:21.146 --> 00:01:24.456
- Back then... - But I heard that was your reason.

00:01:25.286 --> 00:01:28.826
He probably meant that he's the one who isn't good enough for you.

00:01:29.196 --> 00:01:30.956
Not a guy like me who comes from a good family...

00:01:31.326 --> 00:01:33.526
but has a difficult father.

00:01:33.966 --> 00:01:37.936
Nor a guy like Ji Hyuk, too ordinary to be of any help to you.

00:01:41.036 --> 00:01:42.406
So Seong Jae told you.

00:01:44.976 --> 00:01:45.976
That's right.

00:01:47.006 --> 00:01:48.276
That's what I thought.

00:01:50.446 --> 00:01:51.786
Because I cared about you so much.

00:01:52.846 --> 00:01:54.346
And if I meet a man like that...

00:01:56.816 --> 00:01:58.056
I'm supposed to be happy?

00:02:00.926 --> 00:02:04.626
Who are you to set my standards? It's my life, not yours.

00:02:06.696 --> 00:02:08.666
I wanted you to be with someone perfect.

00:02:10.836 --> 00:02:11.966
If that's the case,

00:02:12.566 --> 00:02:14.236
why didn't you tell me the reason back then?

00:02:15.776 --> 00:02:17.936
When I was furious after hearing you were getting married.

00:02:18.206 --> 00:02:20.346
If you'd just said, "Eun Oh, your background..."

00:02:20.346 --> 00:02:21.416
"and circumstances..."

00:02:21.776 --> 00:02:24.716
"don't meet my standards," it would've been so much simpler.

00:02:26.516 --> 00:02:29.086
You let me completely misunderstand you,

00:02:29.816 --> 00:02:32.986
and you never offered an explanation or even an excuse.

00:02:35.056 --> 00:02:36.256
It was because of your ego,

00:02:37.326 --> 00:02:39.096
your need to save face. Isn't that right?

00:02:40.366 --> 00:02:42.096
Especially because you were about to become...

00:02:42.096 --> 00:02:43.196
Haneul Construction's son-in-law.

00:02:46.136 --> 00:02:48.236
In that moment, our ten years together...

00:02:49.136 --> 00:02:51.776
and our friendship where we trusted each other more than anyone...

00:02:53.306 --> 00:02:54.916
were shattered to pieces.

00:02:57.846 --> 00:02:58.886
I'm sorry.

00:03:02.416 --> 00:03:04.056
You're just pathetic.

00:03:07.426 --> 00:03:09.556
What's the point of you liking me now?

00:03:11.356 --> 00:03:12.826
It's all pointless now.

00:03:15.766 --> 00:03:17.096
What do you mean, it's pointless?

00:03:17.996 --> 00:03:21.036
If Jung Bo A hadn't run away from that wedding,

00:03:23.276 --> 00:03:25.306
you'd be the son-in-law of the Haneul Construction family now.

00:03:29.946 --> 00:03:30.946
I guess...

00:03:31.786 --> 00:03:33.446
you'd be the Vice President.

00:03:36.986 --> 00:03:38.586
That kind of person...

00:03:39.286 --> 00:03:40.286
I can't stand them.

00:03:42.026 --> 00:03:45.366
Someone who would marry without love for money...

00:03:48.196 --> 00:03:49.196
I despise people like that.

00:04:01.076 --> 00:04:03.016
I would never let someone like that into my life.

00:04:14.826 --> 00:04:16.096
We really...

00:04:19.196 --> 00:04:20.496
don't belong together.

00:04:30.436 --> 00:04:31.436
Look.

00:04:33.176 --> 00:04:34.846
We're already a broken dish.

00:04:36.376 --> 00:04:39.346
They say you can glue a broken dish back together,

00:04:40.316 --> 00:04:42.416
but you can never use it again.

00:04:46.126 --> 00:04:48.126
Since we're pieced back together in a way,

00:04:50.726 --> 00:04:51.866
let's go back to how we were,

00:04:53.896 --> 00:04:55.736
and just be good colleagues.

00:05:07.806 --> 00:05:09.116
Excuse me.

00:05:11.216 --> 00:05:12.746
Mr. Lee.

00:05:13.386 --> 00:05:14.816
Why weren't you answering your phone?

00:05:16.656 --> 00:05:19.586
The advisory firm has just sent over the AP Group valuation report.

00:05:20.726 --> 00:05:21.726
Right.

00:05:21.996 --> 00:05:25.066
Yes, I've printed it out for you, so please have a look.

00:05:29.096 --> 00:05:31.806
I need to go to Suri-dong and check on the facilities.

00:05:36.036 --> 00:05:37.036
Okay.

00:05:54.756 --> 00:05:55.756
It's over.

00:05:57.956 --> 00:05:58.966
It's all over now.

00:06:20.586 --> 00:06:21.586
Mr. Lee.

00:06:27.456 --> 00:06:28.456
Thanks.

00:07:06.466 --> 00:07:08.026
Ji Hyuk said he wouldn't be coming home tonight.

00:07:08.566 --> 00:07:09.866
I guess he's swamped.

00:07:10.566 --> 00:07:12.106
He's not coming home? What's he so busy with?

00:07:12.536 --> 00:07:14.806
He just said he had to pull an all-nighter at work.

00:07:15.536 --> 00:07:17.976
But he's not in manufacturing. Why would he pull an all-nighter?

00:07:18.546 --> 00:07:21.746
You should've asked for more details on why he can't come home.

00:07:23.416 --> 00:07:26.916
The CEO wouldn't pull an all-nighter unless something happened.

00:07:28.316 --> 00:07:29.316
That kid...

00:07:37.156 --> 00:07:38.726
It looks like he went home.

00:07:42.396 --> 00:07:45.306
- You're here? - You must have worked all night.

00:07:46.106 --> 00:07:47.606
Did you pull an all-nighter too?

00:07:47.606 --> 00:07:49.276
The investment proposal was urgent.

00:07:49.376 --> 00:07:52.246
Cheol Min, I'm going to the bank. Can you get the documents ready?

00:07:52.346 --> 00:07:53.346
Yes, sir.

00:07:55.516 --> 00:07:58.616
I think we can approve the loan for the amount you requested.

00:07:58.846 --> 00:08:00.586
Great. Please proceed.

00:08:01.246 --> 00:08:03.086
Be sure to emphasize that we must integrate our distribution,

00:08:03.086 --> 00:08:04.886
logistics, and construction networks.

00:08:05.126 --> 00:08:07.956
We absolutely must show them that the brand value will increase.

00:08:08.026 --> 00:08:09.456
Next, with this graph...

00:08:09.696 --> 00:08:13.496
As you know, Mamdaerozip has shown consistent and rapid growth.

00:08:14.696 --> 00:08:17.366
The synergy between AP Group and Mamdaerozip...

00:08:17.696 --> 00:08:19.636
is what you're about to witness.

00:08:19.966 --> 00:08:22.436
(Gogossing)

00:08:24.906 --> 00:08:26.306
Here's your delivery.

00:08:27.276 --> 00:08:29.816
How's that burn on your arm doing?

00:08:30.816 --> 00:08:31.946
It's getting better.

00:08:32.286 --> 00:08:33.286
Good.

00:08:33.646 --> 00:08:37.856
Mr. Shin met you at the restaurant. He said you're sharp and very nice.

00:08:38.726 --> 00:08:42.826
I'm new to this field, so please show me the ropes.

00:08:43.256 --> 00:08:46.866
Ms. Jung will show you the ropes before she goes on maternity leave.

00:08:47.466 --> 00:08:48.496
Okay.

00:08:49.166 --> 00:08:53.036
So until she leaves, I just work four hours a day, right?

00:08:56.376 --> 00:08:58.746
(Finding a suitable delivery for Lee Sang Cheol)

00:09:02.446 --> 00:09:05.116
He just said he had to pull an all-nighter at work.

00:09:05.786 --> 00:09:07.686
But he's not in manufacturing. Why would he pull an all-nighter?

