00:09:24.166 --> 00:09:25.166
What?

00:09:25.506 --> 00:09:26.506
What in the world?

00:09:27.036 --> 00:09:28.036
This can't be happening.

00:09:28.636 --> 00:09:29.906
This punk...

00:09:31.976 --> 00:09:32.976
(Ms. Shin)

00:09:32.976 --> 00:09:36.716
Ji Eun Oh's routine hasn't changed. She only goes between work and home.

00:09:38.486 --> 00:09:41.646
Whatever the reason, they still abandoned me.

00:09:43.056 --> 00:09:45.086
What's there to be curious about?

00:09:50.226 --> 00:09:52.396
Of course, you must have a lot on your mind.

00:09:59.666 --> 00:10:00.866
Why do you keep staring at me?

00:10:01.936 --> 00:10:05.006
Didn't you say your business trip was supposed to be two weeks long?

00:10:06.706 --> 00:10:08.746
I guess I must have missed you.

00:10:09.146 --> 00:10:11.416
- Sorry? - I mean...

00:10:11.916 --> 00:10:14.646
Didn't it occur to you that I might have cut my trip short?

00:10:15.416 --> 00:10:19.256
How can you talk of marrying a guy you've only met once?

00:10:19.556 --> 00:10:22.056
Do you even know what food he likes? Have you held his hand?

00:10:22.196 --> 00:10:23.256
Have you kissed him?

00:10:33.136 --> 00:10:35.706
So, I say I missed you, and you get hiccups.

00:10:37.536 --> 00:10:39.276
This should stop them.

00:10:39.546 --> 00:10:40.946
He probably bought you a gift.

00:10:41.646 --> 00:10:44.316
Then you say, "What's this for?"

00:10:44.446 --> 00:10:45.786
What's this for?

00:10:46.486 --> 00:10:48.446
I was thinking of you during my trip.

00:10:49.616 --> 00:10:50.616
Let me put it on for you.

00:10:51.086 --> 00:10:52.726
He'll say he bought it because he was thinking of you.

00:10:52.986 --> 00:10:55.056
- Then... - I'll accept it on my birthday.

00:10:56.126 --> 00:10:58.696
You have to really play up the "new to the dating scene" angle.

00:10:58.696 --> 00:11:00.766
You really haven't dated much, have you, Yeong Ra?

00:11:03.266 --> 00:11:04.436
Please, sit down.

00:11:06.306 --> 00:11:07.766
People are staring.

00:11:15.916 --> 00:11:17.046
Take it.

00:11:17.646 --> 00:11:19.146
I'll get you something even better for your birthday.

00:11:22.816 --> 00:11:24.416
Give this to me on my birthday, then.

00:11:27.186 --> 00:11:30.896
But you can't just act naive. You have to show a mind of your own.

00:11:30.896 --> 00:11:32.466
Receiving gifts for no reason...

00:11:32.926 --> 00:11:34.266
It's not really my thing.

00:11:37.436 --> 00:11:38.706
When is your birthday, then?

00:11:46.306 --> 00:11:48.076
Are they parting ways immediately after the meal?

00:11:49.246 --> 00:11:50.516
Where are they off to?

00:11:55.586 --> 00:11:56.586
What?

00:11:58.486 --> 00:11:59.986
That punk is holding her hand.

00:12:00.586 --> 00:12:02.856
And Yeong Ra's just letting him?

00:12:03.556 --> 00:12:06.226
She lets her mom drag her around. Now, she lets a guy do it too.

00:12:07.296 --> 00:12:08.936
Park Yeong Ra's life, I swear...

00:12:09.436 --> 00:12:10.436
Hey.

00:12:10.696 --> 00:12:13.666
How can you go through life not even knowing who you are?

00:12:13.866 --> 00:12:16.406
For someone so talented at writing and drawing webtoons,

00:12:16.706 --> 00:12:19.076
why can't you use your own talents and live freely?

00:12:30.656 --> 00:12:31.656
What's wrong?

00:12:31.916 --> 00:12:33.326
You must be feeling warm.

00:12:33.926 --> 00:12:34.926
Your hand is a bit sweaty.

00:12:36.426 --> 00:12:37.796
I guess I'm nervous.

00:12:41.796 --> 00:12:43.366
I thought I had some tissues.

00:12:44.366 --> 00:12:46.306
I must have startled you by grabbing your hand like that.

00:12:51.576 --> 00:12:53.106
We've only met twice.

00:12:54.176 --> 00:12:55.246
So of course, it's a little awkward.

00:12:56.316 --> 00:12:57.316
But...

00:12:57.916 --> 00:13:00.546
I was under the impression we're dating with marriage in mind.

00:13:00.786 --> 00:13:02.986
Our families have already worked things out.

00:13:04.616 --> 00:13:06.926
It's not like we've set a date,

00:13:08.226 --> 00:13:10.356
and this is still only our second meeting.

00:13:11.726 --> 00:13:13.226
So I'm not quite comfortable yet.

00:13:16.996 --> 00:13:17.996
Right.

00:13:18.666 --> 00:13:19.736
That's what I like.

00:13:20.166 --> 00:13:22.136
I like that you're not like most girls these days.

00:13:22.536 --> 00:13:24.206
Your mother has managed you very well.

00:13:25.806 --> 00:13:27.746
You said you had a meeting at 2pm, right?

00:13:36.256 --> 00:13:37.256
I'm cold.

00:13:43.196 --> 00:13:44.226
Hey.

00:13:45.566 --> 00:13:47.296
Hey, get her home safe. Got it?

00:13:47.766 --> 00:13:50.436
I hear that stalker is still on the loose, right?

00:13:53.006 --> 00:13:55.876
I'm a salaried employee. I don't accept tips.

00:14:01.646 --> 00:14:03.216
What's with him? The nerve.

00:14:03.546 --> 00:14:07.046
Wow, he has his surprisingly cool moments.

00:14:16.826 --> 00:14:17.926
Darn it!

00:14:32.506 --> 00:14:33.506
What are you doing?

00:14:36.416 --> 00:14:38.216
Your hand is nice and dry.

00:14:44.986 --> 00:14:48.026
Lee Sang Hoon's hand was so clammy. It felt weird.

00:14:48.826 --> 00:14:50.396
Weird, how?

00:14:52.126 --> 00:14:53.666
Good weird or bad weird?

00:14:54.726 --> 00:14:56.996
- Bad, obviously. - It was?

00:14:57.136 --> 00:15:01.606
Hey, that's a big deal. Physical chemistry is important.

00:15:02.176 --> 00:15:03.406
You at least know that much, right?

00:15:10.716 --> 00:15:14.046
You don't? You seriously don't know that?

00:15:14.116 --> 00:15:15.686
No, I know!

00:15:16.056 --> 00:15:17.856
Let me ask you straight out.

00:15:18.486 --> 00:15:21.326
First of all, do you actually want to get married now?

00:15:24.656 --> 00:15:25.666
I don't.

00:15:25.726 --> 00:15:28.796
Then just say no. Tell them he's not the one.

00:15:29.236 --> 00:15:32.506
Don't you know I can't be honest and just say I don't want to do it?

00:15:33.336 --> 00:15:35.806
You're always telling me, "Don't do it," or "You can't."

00:15:36.236 --> 00:15:39.606
- Fine, get married then. - No, that's not what I meant.

00:15:43.576 --> 00:15:44.776
I need to think.

00:15:46.216 --> 00:15:47.246
About what?

00:15:47.686 --> 00:15:48.746
How to handle it.

00:15:55.596 --> 00:15:56.956
How was your date today?

00:15:57.556 --> 00:15:59.866
I heard he even cut his business trip short to see you.

00:16:01.526 --> 00:16:02.866
It was okay.

00:16:03.766 --> 00:16:04.936
It wasn't bad, was it?

00:16:06.006 --> 00:16:07.006
No.

00:16:08.706 --> 00:16:11.376
And we're meeting again next week.

00:16:14.806 --> 00:16:16.316
Good.

00:16:17.646 --> 00:16:18.846
Listen, Yeong Ra.

00:16:19.546 --> 00:16:21.686
If you marry into Jinhwa Group,

00:16:21.686 --> 00:16:24.516
you'll enter a top-20 business family.

00:16:25.856 --> 00:16:27.986
You know this opportunity doesn't come along for just anyone.

00:16:28.826 --> 00:16:33.266
If I'd had your advantages, I could've landed the HO Group heir.

00:16:34.226 --> 00:16:35.226
I know.

00:16:37.236 --> 00:16:41.106
But since I was remarrying and had no family background,

00:16:41.406 --> 00:16:43.306
I was more than grateful to marry your dad.

00:16:45.306 --> 00:16:47.006
But it's different for you.

00:16:48.346 --> 00:16:51.076
In life, there's this thing called synergy.

00:16:52.016 --> 00:16:56.186
It's the combination of your family, looks, age, education, and job...

00:16:56.316 --> 00:16:58.686
that made marrying the son of Jinhwa Group possible.

00:16:59.226 --> 00:17:01.886
And it's how you'll move up in the world.

00:17:04.456 --> 00:17:05.496
Don't you forget it.

00:17:07.526 --> 00:17:10.036
Opportunities like this don't come often for people like us.

00:17:11.836 --> 00:17:13.866
Yes, I know.

00:17:26.616 --> 00:17:28.116
I know. I get it.

00:17:28.516 --> 00:17:30.586
I know we agreed to pretend we don't know each other.

00:17:31.756 --> 00:17:34.086
Then what are you doing in my room?

00:17:34.356 --> 00:17:39.166
Well, even so... I couldn't let this one thing slide.

00:17:40.466 --> 00:17:41.466
What's this about?

00:17:42.266 --> 00:17:44.696
Are you that desperate for money?

00:17:45.596 --> 00:17:49.676
What makes you think you can just take over a huge company like AP?

00:17:49.906 --> 00:17:52.106
Why are you so desperate to hit the jackpot?

00:17:54.376 --> 00:17:56.746
How did you find out about that?

00:17:57.076 --> 00:17:58.346
Is that really what matters right now?

00:18:00.416 --> 00:18:02.146
I'm not trying to take it over for the money.

00:18:02.686 --> 00:18:06.456
I'm not trying to hit the jackpot. So please, don't worry so much.

00:18:06.926 --> 00:18:10.626
How can you not call it greed? A kid like you with no experience...

00:18:10.696 --> 00:18:12.966
thinking he can shoot straight to the top?

00:18:13.026 --> 00:18:14.366
Dad, please...

00:18:16.466 --> 00:18:17.666
Just stop...

00:18:19.766 --> 00:18:21.206
Please, don't do this.

00:18:22.736 --> 00:18:26.476
I'm asking you to stop judging me by your own standards.

00:18:27.506 --> 00:18:29.146
You could be wrong, you know.

00:18:30.446 --> 00:18:31.776
We had an agreement, Dad.

00:18:34.346 --> 00:18:36.586
Just pretend you don't know anything.

00:18:38.356 --> 00:18:39.986
But you're my son...

00:18:40.056 --> 00:18:41.856
I know you're only worried because I'm your son.

00:18:42.596 --> 00:18:44.996
But you always jump straight to judging me.

00:18:45.926 --> 00:18:48.626
And that doesn't help me at all.

00:19:25.296 --> 00:19:27.136
Nice, we're off to a great start.

00:19:27.906 --> 00:19:30.606
And I've got even better news to top it off.

00:19:31.376 --> 00:19:33.706
The only good news I care about is an investment.

00:19:34.506 --> 00:19:38.516
Boyang Construction was on the list of strategic investors.

00:19:38.576 --> 00:19:41.386
- Yes. - They want to invest ten million.

00:19:42.586 --> 00:19:44.456
Boyang Construction is offering ten million dollars?

00:19:46.026 --> 00:19:47.956
You heard the amount we're prepared to invest?

00:19:48.686 --> 00:19:49.726
Ten million dollars.

00:19:50.256 --> 00:19:51.296
Thank you.

00:19:51.796 --> 00:19:53.796
I've finally found a partner who believes in me.

00:19:54.596 --> 00:19:56.296
You've reviewed the investment terms, right?

00:19:59.306 --> 00:20:00.366
Are the terms acceptable?

00:20:01.366 --> 00:20:03.136
Yes, there don't seem to be any particular issues.

00:20:03.436 --> 00:20:05.776
In that case, shall we draw up the letter of intent now?

00:20:07.546 --> 00:20:08.746
That was a quick decision.

00:20:09.446 --> 00:20:12.376
- Please have the contract ready. - Sure.

00:20:41.046 --> 00:20:42.546
What brings you here?

00:20:44.976 --> 00:20:45.986
No reason.

00:20:48.716 --> 00:20:49.716
Feel free to look around.

00:20:55.786 --> 00:20:57.556
Your clients must love this place.

00:21:00.826 --> 00:21:01.996
Why is he here?

00:21:03.636 --> 00:21:04.866
Here...

00:21:06.806 --> 00:21:07.936
Just in case.

00:21:14.806 --> 00:21:15.806
I'm leaving.

00:22:11.036 --> 00:22:12.096
This is good.

