00:39:40.586 --> 00:39:43.346
It's because I've lived too long with nothing to do.

00:39:44.816 --> 00:39:45.816
Dad.

00:39:49.756 --> 00:39:50.826
Dad.

00:39:51.756 --> 00:39:52.996
I'm sorry.

00:39:53.556 --> 00:39:54.566
Dad...

00:40:10.276 --> 00:40:11.276
Thanks.

00:40:12.076 --> 00:40:13.646
You were really thorough with the special provisions.

00:40:18.186 --> 00:40:20.656
Hey, I actually heard an update from Sung Guk.

00:40:21.656 --> 00:40:22.656
With Boyang Construction.

00:40:23.896 --> 00:40:25.096
Honestly, I didn't think it would work out,

00:40:25.356 --> 00:40:26.626
but you've already made it over the hump.

00:40:27.096 --> 00:40:28.096
We've still got a long way to go.

00:40:28.396 --> 00:40:29.826
Hey, you're practically there.

00:40:30.666 --> 00:40:32.836
Honestly, I never imagined you'd get this far.

00:40:33.966 --> 00:40:34.966
That's incredible, Lee Ji Hyuk.

00:40:39.606 --> 00:40:40.606
Thank you, and...

00:40:42.206 --> 00:40:43.206
I'm sorry.

00:40:47.116 --> 00:40:48.116
Okay, "thanks" for the investment.

00:40:48.786 --> 00:40:49.786
And what are you sorry for?

00:40:52.886 --> 00:40:54.786
I confessed my feelings to Eun Oh.

00:40:55.486 --> 00:40:56.486
I couldn't wait for you.

00:41:04.036 --> 00:41:05.036
You got shot down, didn't you?

00:41:06.296 --> 00:41:07.306
Yes.

00:41:09.536 --> 00:41:12.436
So that's what it feels like when you can't hold back.

00:41:14.346 --> 00:41:16.946
You confessed even though you knew she'd turn you down?

00:41:19.576 --> 00:41:20.586
It just happened.

00:41:25.386 --> 00:41:28.226
But don't feel bad on my account.

00:41:30.256 --> 00:41:31.856
Because I'm not going to confess to Eun Oh.

00:41:33.156 --> 00:41:34.166
What?

00:41:35.266 --> 00:41:38.536
I've thought long and hard about why I even like Eun Oh.

00:41:39.966 --> 00:41:42.436
Hey, do you remember why we became friends?

00:41:44.776 --> 00:41:45.776
The sneakers?

00:41:46.736 --> 00:41:48.946
Hey, why are you bringing that up now?

00:41:49.276 --> 00:41:50.716
No, it's all related.

00:41:52.776 --> 00:41:53.786
Now, you've got me curious.

00:41:54.016 --> 00:41:55.046
Go on.

00:41:55.716 --> 00:41:58.686
When they took my sneakers before, I'd just give them up.

00:41:59.256 --> 00:42:00.486
Three times to the three of them.

00:42:01.086 --> 00:42:02.086
But...

00:42:02.786 --> 00:42:04.426
I couldn't let them take my sneakers that day.

00:42:05.296 --> 00:42:06.926
Because my stepmother deliberately made me wear them.

00:42:09.166 --> 00:42:10.166
What's that supposed to mean?

00:42:11.166 --> 00:42:12.896
She wanted my father to find out...

00:42:13.766 --> 00:42:15.566
that I was being bullied.

00:42:16.306 --> 00:42:17.306
Wear these today.

00:42:17.676 --> 00:42:20.336
These are the limited-edition collaboration sneakers.

00:42:20.646 --> 00:42:22.006
Aren't they pretty?

00:42:23.246 --> 00:42:25.246
I like wearing these.

00:42:26.746 --> 00:42:28.516
I know your shoes got swapped by mistake,

00:42:28.516 --> 00:42:29.886
but you can't keep wearing those worn-out shoes.

00:42:31.086 --> 00:42:33.856
If your dad finds out, you'll be in big trouble.

00:42:35.286 --> 00:42:37.696
But these... They're too nice.

00:42:38.596 --> 00:42:41.966
It's a foreign brand kids don't know.

00:42:41.966 --> 00:42:43.566
They just look fancy.

00:42:48.566 --> 00:42:49.566
I won't tell him...

00:42:49.836 --> 00:42:52.506
that you lost your shoes several times.

00:42:52.836 --> 00:42:53.846
I'll keep it a secret.

00:42:55.506 --> 00:42:56.876
Seriously, not these ones.

00:42:57.576 --> 00:42:59.576
- If they find out I lost these... - Then what?

00:43:00.116 --> 00:43:01.316
Are you going to call your mommy?

00:43:02.486 --> 00:43:03.616
I already gave you three pairs of sneakers.

00:43:04.256 --> 00:43:05.256
And they were all brand new.

00:43:06.316 --> 00:43:07.686
Please, just not this pair.

00:43:08.726 --> 00:43:10.556
I'll get you an extra 30 dollars from my allowance on Monday.

00:43:11.226 --> 00:43:12.926
- You punk. - No. Please, no!

00:43:13.326 --> 00:43:15.896
What do you mean, "no?" Come on!

00:43:16.826 --> 00:43:18.236
And that's when you saved me.

00:43:19.466 --> 00:43:21.506
You saved me from my stepmother's trap,

00:43:22.106 --> 00:43:25.076
and your parents showed me what a real loving family is.

00:43:25.736 --> 00:43:26.736
I was so envious.

00:43:27.946 --> 00:43:30.916
Wait. She deliberately tried to let your father know...

00:43:30.976 --> 00:43:32.646
that you were being bullied?

00:43:33.076 --> 00:43:34.086
But why?

00:43:35.016 --> 00:43:37.256
You know how my father hated me for being weak.

00:43:37.786 --> 00:43:39.986
If he'd found out his son was being bullied,

00:43:40.286 --> 00:43:42.456
he would've stormed into school and made a huge fuss.

00:43:42.786 --> 00:43:44.426
Sure, the bullying might've stopped, but...

00:43:45.196 --> 00:43:47.226
my father would've become even more controlling and suffocating,

00:43:48.426 --> 00:43:50.466
and I would have ended up on my stepmother's...

00:43:50.966 --> 00:43:51.966
invisible leash.

00:43:53.236 --> 00:43:54.236
That's right.

00:43:54.806 --> 00:43:57.506
You did say your stepmother was cold.

00:43:58.276 --> 00:43:59.376
But I had no idea it was that bad.

00:43:59.836 --> 00:44:00.846
And you know what's terrifying?

00:44:01.206 --> 00:44:04.016
She smiles, but there's no warmth. It's chilling.

00:44:05.146 --> 00:44:06.276
And yet, she's perfect at everything.

00:44:07.486 --> 00:44:10.116
She even made someone like my father trust her completely.

00:44:13.686 --> 00:44:16.286
My whole life with my stepmother...

00:44:16.356 --> 00:44:18.296
has been like walking on eggshells.

00:44:19.656 --> 00:44:20.796
I can't let on that I hate her,

00:44:21.726 --> 00:44:23.226
but I can't pretend to like her either.

00:44:24.096 --> 00:44:25.096
I'm scared she'll see through me.

00:44:28.166 --> 00:44:29.206
Man...

00:44:30.266 --> 00:44:31.736
It looks like you kept a lot from me, too.

00:44:32.536 --> 00:44:34.506
I mean, you should have at least vented to me.

00:44:35.306 --> 00:44:36.946
But then I met Ji Eun Oh.

00:44:37.976 --> 00:44:40.786
From the moment I met her, I knew Eun Oh was different.

00:44:41.646 --> 00:44:42.886
It was winter at the time,

00:44:43.586 --> 00:44:45.256
but she was so warm and comforting.

00:44:46.656 --> 00:44:47.786
So bright and full of life.

00:44:48.326 --> 00:44:49.326
She really was.

00:44:50.696 --> 00:44:51.696
That's just who she is.

00:44:52.126 --> 00:44:53.126
She really is.

00:44:54.726 --> 00:44:55.866
I was just in awe of her.

00:44:57.266 --> 00:44:58.966
I thought, "I want to love someone like that."

00:44:59.866 --> 00:45:01.966
"I wish a woman like her could be mine."

00:45:02.666 --> 00:45:04.176
But like you said,

00:45:04.376 --> 00:45:06.376
it'd be long-distance, so I couldn't say anything.

00:45:07.476 --> 00:45:10.376
And I figured I didn't deserve her, since I'm divorced.

00:45:11.276 --> 00:45:12.416
And more than anything,

00:45:13.116 --> 00:45:15.046
I was afraid she'd get dragged into my family's messy drama.

00:45:16.016 --> 00:45:17.956
I thought that's why I couldn't bring myself to confess.

00:45:23.686 --> 00:45:24.726
But it wasn't love.

00:45:26.296 --> 00:45:27.896
I managed to hold back, after all.

00:45:30.596 --> 00:45:31.696
Maybe...

00:45:33.096 --> 00:45:35.736
I think I just liked the idea of myself...

00:45:36.866 --> 00:45:37.876
being in love with someone.

00:45:45.246 --> 00:45:46.346
So?

00:45:46.846 --> 00:45:48.186
That's how I've sorted out my feelings.

00:45:48.946 --> 00:45:49.946
So what are you going to do?

00:45:51.986 --> 00:45:54.256
I can't think straight. It's too complicated.

00:45:54.986 --> 00:45:55.986
Why?

00:45:56.356 --> 00:45:57.496
You won't even talk to me about it?

00:45:58.596 --> 00:46:00.866
I only told you all this to clear up the misunderstanding.

00:46:03.426 --> 00:46:04.666
That's not the issue.

00:46:05.936 --> 00:46:06.936
I'm cornered.

00:46:08.106 --> 00:46:09.936
Then you'd better go all-in on the AP acquisition.

00:46:12.376 --> 00:46:15.276
At least I have that, I guess.

00:46:17.146 --> 00:46:18.676
Oh, right. The Preliminary Bid is tomorrow, isn't it?

00:46:19.416 --> 00:46:20.416
Just focus on your work.

00:46:20.716 --> 00:46:22.386
I'm saying this as your friend, not an investor.

00:46:24.516 --> 00:46:25.656
All right.

00:46:26.256 --> 00:46:27.256
I'll be in touch.

00:46:29.026 --> 00:46:30.696
(Shoealls)

00:46:39.836 --> 00:46:40.836
I feel relieved.

00:46:43.106 --> 00:46:44.276
But it looks like Ji Hyuk's in real trouble.

00:46:50.846 --> 00:46:53.116
(Store Manager Choi In Sook)

00:46:54.016 --> 00:46:56.946
- Hello, Park Seong Jae speaking. - Director, what am I going to do?

00:46:57.346 --> 00:46:59.086
I really don't know what to do with Su Bin.

00:46:59.716 --> 00:47:00.726
What's going on?

00:47:01.186 --> 00:47:02.756
- Thank you. - Have a good day.

00:47:02.826 --> 00:47:03.886
Have a good one!

00:47:11.566 --> 00:47:13.396
Su Bin. It's 6pm.

00:47:13.866 --> 00:47:16.736
Thank you so much for today. You were a great help with the rush.

00:47:19.206 --> 00:47:20.806
Is it that late already?

00:47:21.706 --> 00:47:24.216
We had so many customers, I lost all track of time.

00:47:25.746 --> 00:47:29.886
I was panicking about that huge tour group booking.

00:47:30.346 --> 00:47:33.056
It would've been a disaster if you weren't here.

00:47:33.486 --> 00:47:36.926
Min Ji, just let me know if you need help again.

00:47:38.626 --> 00:47:40.196
I learned so much from you.

00:47:41.066 --> 00:47:43.126
Thanks again for your help.

00:47:48.806 --> 00:47:49.806
Oh, this.

00:47:54.176 --> 00:47:56.206
- Are you okay? - I'm fine.

00:48:04.816 --> 00:48:07.316
- Great work today. Good night. - You too. See you next time.

00:48:07.386 --> 00:48:09.256
- Great work. - You too.

00:48:14.396 --> 00:48:16.496
We submitted the Preliminary Bid today.

00:48:18.166 --> 00:48:19.696
Oh, you did?

00:48:20.596 --> 00:48:21.766
I really hope it goes well.

00:48:28.046 --> 00:48:29.606
Why is he giving me a report?

00:48:30.106 --> 00:48:31.446
Is he just clueless or what?

00:48:38.416 --> 00:48:39.416
Hey, what's up?

00:48:40.686 --> 00:48:41.686
Eun Oh.

00:48:43.156 --> 00:48:44.256
There's something I need to tell you.

00:48:44.856 --> 00:48:45.856
What is it?

00:48:45.996 --> 00:48:50.066
Remember I said Ji Hyuk offered me a PR and marketing position?

00:48:51.766 --> 00:48:52.766
A recruitment offer.

00:48:53.036 --> 00:48:55.066
How about you run our company's PR and marketing?

00:48:55.866 --> 00:48:58.736
You learned filming and editing to become a movie director, right?

00:48:59.206 --> 00:49:00.536
And you wouldn't have to come in every day.

00:49:01.176 --> 00:49:03.606
It's full-time with benefits, and you can work from home.

00:49:03.946 --> 00:49:04.946
Work from home?

00:49:05.146 --> 00:49:07.916
I wasn't expecting that. That's really tempting.

00:49:09.516 --> 00:49:13.316
But is that the only reason? I mean, this is so out of the blue.

00:49:14.186 --> 00:49:17.086
The company needs someone for PR and marketing.

00:49:18.796 --> 00:49:20.966
And I thought it'd be great for you and Eun Oh to work together.

00:49:22.496 --> 00:49:24.866
Since you two are so close.

00:49:26.266 --> 00:49:29.306
Are you really going to all this trouble for Eun Oh?

00:49:30.836 --> 00:49:32.276
What? What are you talking about?

00:49:32.536 --> 00:49:35.076
Anyway, think it over and let me know later.

00:49:37.946 --> 00:49:39.046
That's when I knew.

00:49:39.816 --> 00:49:41.486
That Ji Hyuk likes you.

00:49:46.386 --> 00:49:47.386
I see.

00:49:49.086 --> 00:49:52.026
Ji Eun Oh, I'm telling you, Ji Hyuk likes you.

00:49:55.496 --> 00:49:56.496
I know.

00:49:57.166 --> 00:49:58.166
How?

00:49:59.696 --> 00:50:01.766
Did Ji Hyuk actually confess to you?

00:50:02.166 --> 00:50:03.166
My gosh.

00:50:03.706 --> 00:50:06.906
How can you act like it's nothing? Now that he's told you he likes you.

00:50:08.876 --> 00:50:09.876
Su Jeong.

00:50:10.476 --> 00:50:11.916
You once told me...

00:50:12.676 --> 00:50:16.516
that when you like someone, you get to know yourself better.

00:50:16.646 --> 00:50:17.656
Yes.

00:50:18.086 --> 00:50:21.586
I've learned a lot too, after everything with Ji Hyuk.

00:50:22.056 --> 00:50:23.256
I've had a lot of realisations.

00:50:23.456 --> 00:50:24.656
Like what?

00:50:25.826 --> 00:50:27.496
That timing is everything.

00:50:29.166 --> 00:50:30.166
That liking someone...

00:50:30.666 --> 00:50:33.336
isn't always some huge, dramatic thing.

00:50:34.196 --> 00:50:35.736
And even if it felt like a huge deal,

00:50:36.136 --> 00:50:38.436
things can change over time.

00:50:40.036 --> 00:50:43.876
A crush doesn't mean it'll work out. And just because you like them,

00:50:45.176 --> 00:50:49.046
it doesn't mean they're the one. Stuff like that.

00:50:51.116 --> 00:50:53.056
So, what's your conclusion?

00:50:57.256 --> 00:50:58.896
From now on, Ji Hyuk and I...

00:50:59.496 --> 00:51:01.766
I want us to go back to being good friends like before.

00:51:03.726 --> 00:51:06.866
But really? You don't have any lingering feelings at all?

00:51:07.296 --> 00:51:08.736
I mean, you used to hate him.

00:51:09.266 --> 00:51:11.876
But there's a thin line between love and hate.

00:51:14.236 --> 00:51:15.476
I don't hate him anymore.

00:51:16.046 --> 00:51:17.046
Not at all.

00:51:18.946 --> 00:51:21.386
It's so ironic, though.

00:51:22.016 --> 00:51:25.656
When we talked the other day, you sounded like you had some news,

00:51:25.916 --> 00:51:28.526
so I wondered if something was up with you and Ji Hyuk.

00:51:31.196 --> 00:51:33.226
I did have something I wanted to talk to you about,

00:51:34.596 --> 00:51:35.596
but I've already made my decision.

00:51:35.896 --> 00:51:36.896
About what?

00:51:41.206 --> 00:51:42.806
(Guide to Requesting Disclosure of Adoption Information)

00:51:47.036 --> 00:51:49.006
(Ji Eun Oh has been confirmed as having no known relatives.)

00:51:51.646 --> 00:51:53.516
(Certificate of Genetic Testing for Adoptee with No Known Kin)

00:51:54.146 --> 00:51:57.756
So you have to take this to the police station?

00:51:59.856 --> 00:52:00.856
Yes.

00:52:06.996 --> 00:52:08.926
Su Bin, here's your hourly pay plus a bonus.

00:52:09.666 --> 00:52:11.096
No, it's okay.

00:52:11.536 --> 00:52:13.596
I wasn't expecting anything for helping out.

00:52:14.136 --> 00:52:18.406
You boosted sales so much, I can't just let it go unrewarded.

00:52:18.576 --> 00:52:19.576
Take it.

00:52:20.036 --> 00:52:21.976
Wearing them is the best way to thank me.

00:52:22.346 --> 00:52:25.846
If you ever need an extra hand, feel free to give me a call.

00:52:26.816 --> 00:52:28.586
I'll get going.

00:52:28.986 --> 00:52:30.816
- You got this. - You too.

00:52:31.316 --> 00:52:32.316
Go on.

00:52:43.466 --> 00:52:44.466
Seong Jae.

00:52:48.666 --> 00:52:50.206
(Shoealls)

00:53:00.146 --> 00:53:01.146
Seong Jae!

00:53:04.346 --> 00:53:07.656
- Seong Jae! - What?

00:53:08.656 --> 00:53:10.886
You scared me. Why are you yelling?

00:53:10.986 --> 00:53:12.756
You're the one making me yell!

00:53:14.226 --> 00:53:15.796
Why don't you ever listen to me?

00:53:16.666 --> 00:53:19.666
Why do you keep coming here? I thought you said you'd quit.

00:53:19.936 --> 00:53:22.306
I told you. I'm training Min Ji to take over.

00:53:22.866 --> 00:53:24.636
Why are you bothering with that?

00:53:25.136 --> 00:53:26.506
I told you to quit.

00:53:27.076 --> 00:53:28.506
Did you forget you fought with her?

00:53:28.876 --> 00:53:31.276
She formally apologised.

00:53:33.446 --> 00:53:34.886
How can you be so naive?

00:53:35.616 --> 00:53:36.786
And that's supposed to be an answer?

00:53:37.386 --> 00:53:39.016
You said you'd quit, but you keep showing up?

00:53:40.756 --> 00:53:44.086
It was a really busy day for the store,

00:53:44.226 --> 00:53:46.026
so I was planning on this being my last day.

00:53:46.196 --> 00:53:48.296
Exactly. Why is that your problem?

00:53:49.166 --> 00:53:50.266
Don't you have your own work to do?

00:53:51.096 --> 00:53:53.836
Your channel is doing great, and your subscribers have shot up.

00:53:54.666 --> 00:53:56.636
You have your own thing going on, so why do you keep coming here?

00:53:57.136 --> 00:53:58.736
Why are you making things so hard on yourself?

00:54:01.606 --> 00:54:02.606
That's what I'm wondering.

00:54:03.746 --> 00:54:04.746
What?

00:54:05.376 --> 00:54:07.746
Seriously, why haven't I quit this place?

00:54:09.046 --> 00:54:12.016
- Why couldn't I quit? - Hey, listen.

00:54:12.986 --> 00:54:14.186
It must be because of you.

00:54:16.526 --> 00:54:17.526
What?

00:54:19.056 --> 00:54:20.056
I...

00:54:21.026 --> 00:54:22.296
I think I like you.

00:54:24.196 --> 00:54:25.196
Hey, Lee Su Bin.

00:54:25.196 --> 00:54:27.736
I thought I was just working hard because it's your company,

00:54:28.866 --> 00:54:29.866
but that's not it.

00:54:30.866 --> 00:54:33.836
When I'm here, you sometimes come by,

00:54:33.936 --> 00:54:35.206
and we get to talk.

00:54:40.076 --> 00:54:41.516
I like you, Seong Jae.

00:54:56.096 --> 00:54:57.096
What is this?

00:54:57.896 --> 00:54:59.466
So, you've decided to pivot back to me now?

00:55:00.536 --> 00:55:02.236
Did I seem like an easier target than the weirdos...

00:55:02.236 --> 00:55:03.606
you met through the matchmaking agency?

00:55:04.136 --> 00:55:06.936
Is that why you dragged me out here? Just to pull this stunt?

00:55:07.076 --> 00:55:08.276
Are you done?

00:55:09.076 --> 00:55:10.346
You're divorced.

00:55:11.346 --> 00:55:15.446
My family is ordinary, so it's true I wanted a man with good prospects.

00:55:16.286 --> 00:55:17.416
But I told you...

00:55:18.086 --> 00:55:20.086
I wasn't just after money.

00:55:20.786 --> 00:55:22.626
A divorced guy wouldn't make the list.

00:55:22.626 --> 00:55:24.626
No matter how rich they are, divorced men...

00:55:24.726 --> 00:55:27.226
- are automatically out. - Exactly.

00:55:28.966 --> 00:55:30.296
So get a grip.

00:55:32.536 --> 00:55:33.936
I am divorced.

00:55:34.966 --> 00:55:37.766
I'm Ji Hyuk's friend, and you're his youngest sister,

00:55:37.836 --> 00:55:39.936
which makes you like a little sister to me, too.

00:55:41.546 --> 00:55:43.876
I don't care if your feelings are genuine or not.

00:55:45.416 --> 00:55:47.246
So if you ever say something so ridiculous again,

00:55:48.516 --> 00:55:50.416
I won't even see you as Ji Hyuk's sister anymore.

00:55:51.886 --> 00:55:53.016
So don't you ever...

00:55:58.456 --> 00:55:59.556
I'll take you home.

